ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Don't take it unless you have to.

I would recommend the course to another student. All in all, there seemed to be a lot of resources available to students who might be having trouble. With office hours, instructors, the textbook, and the always accessible videos, there was a support system in play.
I would definitely recommend Math 115. It is a rewarding class where the workload is manageable and you learn a lot.

I would recommend Math 115 to students who are interested in learning calculus as prerequisites for majors for other courses and to really take advantage of shopping period to find a professor that works at a pace that they are comfortable with.
I would recommend this class to anyone who is actually interested in moving forward and taking higher level math courses.
It's a good class! I'm not a math major, so for someone who isn't looking at math (or STEM in general), it's a fine class to take, especially if you want to take care of the QR requirement.

I would recommend Math 115 02 to a fellow student. It provided a concise review of AP Calculus BC material and introduced some more advanced calculus concepts. Furthermore, the information covered in this course was relevant to other classes I took this semester such as Econ 115.
